> Is it possible to put a screen-capture command in the SysRq stuff? when the
> kernel panics, it'd be nice to capture the screen it died on without having
> to spend ten minutes with pencil+paper...
Once it has paniced its a bit late and capture to disk might not be safe
There are 3) answers
1.	Serial console
2.	Use a digital camera (yes I've even had people mail me jpgs of a crash)
3.	if you need to use pen/paper then 99% of the time the only values you
	need are the EIP and the call trace.
